The paper deals with the problem of learning invariances in data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of permanent random connectomes also suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmarks, which suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
